This project is an individual COMP3011 Coursework 2 submission.

Assessment target:
Outstanding mark, 80–100.

Core required functionality:
- Crawl https://quotes.toscrape.com/
- Respect 6-second politeness delay between live requests.
- Build an inverted index.
- Store word frequency and word positions per page.
- Save and load index from file system.
- Provide CLI commands: build, load, print, find.
- Support single-word and multi-word queries.
- Handle edge cases gracefully.

Outstanding features to support:
- TF-IDF ranking.
- Phrase search using word positions.
- Query suggestions for unknown words.
- Benchmarking for build/search time.
- Strong test coverage above 85%.
- Clean README and documented design rationale.

Architecture expectations:
- crawler.py handles fetching pages and following links.
- parser.py extracts meaningful page content.
- tokenizer.py normalises text into tokens.
- indexer.py builds the inverted index.
- storage.py saves and loads index files.
- search.py handles query processing.
- ranking.py handles TF-IDF or scoring logic.
- cli.py handles command-line interaction.
- main.py starts the shell.

Testing expectations:
- Mock network requests where possible.
- Do not make live network calls in most tests.
- Test crawler behaviour separately from parser/indexer logic.
- Test empty queries, missing index file, unknown words, punctuation, case-insensitivity, multi-word search, and phrase search.
- Add integration tests for build/load/print/find behaviour.

Code quality expectations:
- Use type hints.
- Use docstrings.
- Keep functions short.
- Avoid duplicated logic.
- Return clear errors instead of crashing.
- Avoid hardcoded paths except through constants/config.
- Use pathlib for file paths.
- Use logging or clear CLI messages where appropriate.

AI-use expectation:
Every major AI-assisted design or debugging step should be recorded in docs/genai_log.md with:
- Date
- Tool used
- Prompt summary
- AI suggestion
- What I accepted
- What I changed or rejected
- What I learned